did.unittitle: Georgia House of Representatives Communications Office Records

repository.corpname: Richard B. Russell Library for Political Research and Studies

did.abstract: The Georgia House of Representatives Communications Office, previously known as the Georgia House Public Information Office, provides media credentials and workspace for journalists who cover the Georgia House of Representatives. The Director of Media Relations for House Communications, under the direction of the Director of Media Services, supervises the Communications staff to facilitate the coverage by reporters of legislative activity. The staff provides bill texts and reports of pending legislation and disseminates press releases and calendars of business to accredited reporters. In addition, the office maintains taped excerpts from floor debates and online daily activity feeds. The majority of the collection consists of audio recordings (see separate AV finding aid) documenting the regular and special sessions of the Georgia House of Representatives, as well as some Senate proceedings, and photographs maintained by the House photographer. This collection includes biographical sketches of legislators, legislative reports, speeches, research materials, press releases, slide show scripts, audiovisual materials and photographs.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The House Communications Office, previously known as the Georgia House Public Information Office, provides media credentials and workspace for journalists who cover the Georgia House of Representatives and serves as the direct liaison between the Office of the Speaker and media outlets in the state. The Director of Media Relations for House Communications, under the direction of the Director of Media Services, supervises the Communications staff to facilitate the coverage by reporters of legislative activity.

Communications staff provides bill texts and reports of pending legislation and disseminates press releases and calendars of business to accredited reporters. A Daily Report is prepared for Members of the House, the press corps, and House staff detailing the legislative action of the House.

In addition, the office maintains the system on which taped excerpts from floor debates are recorded for audio pickups by radio stations. Daily activity feeds are also available through the Georgia Legislative Network.
Information from the Georgia House Communication’s website, http://www.legis.ga.gov/legis/2007_08/house/communications/communicationmain.htm.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The Georgia House of Representatives Communications Office Records document the relationship between the House and local and national media outlets. Series VII: Photographs and VIII: Audiovisual Materials (see separate AV finding aid) account for the bulk of the collection and document the regular and special sessions of the Georgia House of Representatives. The audio reels primarily document the daily activities on the floor of the House during regular and special sessions from 1975 to 1998. The audio cassettes, from 1974 to 2004, focus more extensively on budget hearings and committee meetings, most notably those of the Appropriations Committee. Biographical sketches, press releases, directories and photographs document House members from 1975 to 2003. The collection also includes speech outlines, research files, slides, and scripts maintained by the office to assist House members with the creation of presentations. The majority of this collection highlights the years 1975 to 2000; however, the collection at large spans over three decades from 1971 to 2006.

arrangement.head: Organization and Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is organized into eight series: I. Legislative Reports; II. Press Relations/Media Activities; III. Member Files; IV. Speech Files; V. Research Files; VI. Presentations; and VII. Photographs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series is organized into three sub-series: A. Weekly Reports, B. Final Reports, and C. Highlights/Session Speeches.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Ninety-one weekly reports summarizing the activities and significant legislation debated and voted upon in the Georgia House of Representatives from 1987 to 2002, with gaps between 1996 and 2002. Several of the files include daily reports and press releases associated with the weekly events.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: The final reports include twenty-one session summaries, between 1975 and 1996, which recap the most discussed legislation and events of each session. Missing from this sub-series are the final reports for 1978, 1982, and 1983.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: The highlights/session speeches include thirty-two files of session highlights, pre- and post-session speeches and pre-session issue lists. The pre-session issue lists include the various topics that may be covered in the coming session and are presented in speech form to assist House members in creating presentations. This sub-series lacks information for the years 1978 to 1979, 1982 to 1984, and 1997.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Press Relations/Media Activities are organized into three sub-series: A. Credentials, B. Press Releases, and C. Radio Scripts. The majority of this series is comprised of over 500 press releases related to various topics including fishing and recreation, vocational education, healthcare, taxes and the state budget, transportation, and water use and conservation.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: The credentials sub-series consists of five folders, arranged chronologically, containing requests and forms for floor passes, photographer passes and news media passes.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This sub-series, arranged chronologically, contains press releases, which keep the media current on House events that are of news value, contain 531 individual announcements dated between 1983 and 2003, the majority between 1985 and 1996.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Member Files are organized into three sub-series based on item type: A. Biographical Files, B. Photographs, and C. Directories. The photographic materials have been separated from the biographical files for the purpose of preservation; however, both biographical files and the corresponding photographs are arranged alphabetically by the member’s last name and are cross referenced. Additional photographs of Georgia House of Representative members and events are located in Series VII: Photographs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This sub-series is arranged alphabetically and includes House members’ biographical sketches, press releases, and speeches. Corresponding photographs have been separated for preservation purposes and may be found in sub-series B. Photographs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This sub-series is arranged alphabetically and includes black and white and color photographs and negatives of members of the Georgia House of Representatives. These photographs have been removed from the Biographical Files for the purpose of preservation. Additional photographs of House members and events are located in Series VII: Photographs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains eighty-three speech files arranged alphabetically by topic. These speeches, maintained by the communications office, are intended to assist members with the creation of presentations. The speeches deal with various topics related to Georgia including education, forestry, medicine, transportation, taxes, and women in business. A majority of these speeches are undated and unassociated with a particular member.
